-- 1. [Problem Restatement] Find the product abc of the coefficients of P(x)=x³+ax²+bx+c whose roots are cos(2π⁄7), cos(4π⁄7), cos(6π⁄7). 2. [Key Idea] Use Vieta’s formulas (abc = (−a)(b)(−c)=S₁S₂S₃) and evaluate the elementary symmetric sums S₁, S₂, S₃ of the three cosines with root-of-unity algebra. 3. [Proof] Let r₁ = cos(2π⁄7), r₂ = cos(4π⁄7), r₃ = cos(6π⁄7), and denote S₁ = r₁+r₂+r₃, S₂ = r₁r₂+r₂r₃+r₃r₁, S₃ = r₁r₂r₃. Step 1. S₁. Because cos(π−θ)=−cos θ, r₁+r₂+r₃ = −[cos(π⁄7)+cos(3π⁄7)+cos(5π⁄7)] = −½, hence S₁ = −½. Step 2. S₂. (r₁+r₂+r₃)² = r₁²+r₂²+r₃² + 2S₂. Using cos²θ = (1+cos 2θ)/2, r₁²+r₂²+r₃² = 3/2 + ½(r₁+r₂+r₃) = 3/2 − ¼ = 5/4. Thus S₂ = ( (−½)² − 5/4 ) / 2 = (1/4 − 5/4)/2 = −½. Step 3. S₃. Let ζ = e^{2πi/7}. Then r_k = (ζ^k+ζ^{−k})/2, so 8S₃ = (ζ+ζ^{−1})(ζ²+ζ^{−2})(ζ³+ζ^{−3}) = (ζ+ζ^{6})(ζ²+ζ^{5})(ζ³+ζ^{4}) = 1 (routine multiplication and the fact ∑_{k=0}^{6}ζ^k=0). Hence S₃ = 1/8. Step 4. Product abc. By Vieta, a = −S₁, b = S₂, c = −S₃, so abc = (−S₁)(S₂)(−S₃) = S₁S₂S₃ = (−½)(−½)(1/8) = 1/32. 4. [Conclusion] Therefore abc = 1/32, confirming choice (D).
